}}\n[[File:Lava scale detail.png|left|150px]]\n'''Lava scales''' are always dropped by [[lava dragon]]s at the [[Lava Dragon Isle]] located in the [[Wilderness]]. They are also dropped uncommonly by [[brutal black dragon]]s. The shards are an ingredient for [[extended antifire]] and [[extended super antifire]] potions.\n\nLava scales themselves have no use, but when ground with a [[pestle and mortar]], players will obtain 3-6 [[lava scale shard]]s, or 6-9 with the completion of the [[Wilderness Diary#Hard|Hard Wilderness Diary]]. The amount is random, with high [[Herblore]] level yielding a higher average.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/449174420670906368|date=27 March 2014|archiveurl=https://archive.is/J7Frk|archivedate=29 May 2020|quote=It's random between 3 and 6, with high Herblore being an advantage.}} With 99 Herblore, players almost always receive the maximum amount with a rare chance of getting fewer.\n\nIf asking [[Wesley]] to grind them, he can only crush one scale to three shards, warning the player of this before proceeding.\n\nNote: If attempting to obtain lava scale shards, [[Infernal eel]] fishing is a viable option for players wishing to avoid the wilderness.\n==Products==\n{{Uses material list|Lava scale}}\n==Item sources==\n{{Drop sources|Lava scale}}\n\n==Changes==\n{{Subject changes header}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 5 March 2015\n|update = Achievement Diaries\n|poll = Old School Achievement Diary Rewards Poll\n|change = You now receive 50% more [[Lava scale shard|shards]] per scale if you have completed the [[Wilderness Hard Diary]].\n}}\n{{Subject changes footer}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Herblore secondaries}}"}